			<div class="content" id="post-content-1122414">
									

<p>Why, yes. Happily. I'll grab the first paragraph of the description for starters.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-939 are endothermic, chiefly carnivorous pack-based predators adapted for life within high humidity, low light environments such as caves, displaying atrophy of various systems consistent with such a habitat. The skin of SCP-939 is a translucent red, owing not to pigmentation but a compound chemically similar to hemoglobin, and is highly permeable to moisture. SCP-939 average 215cm tall standing upright and weigh an average of 250kg with a lithe build, though weight is highly variable. Each of their four limbs end in three-fingered claws with a fourth, opposable digit. The pads of their claws are covered in setae which grant them considerable climbing abilities. Their heads are elongated and devoid of even vestigial eyes or eye sockets and contain no brain casing. Four nostrils, forming the vertexes of an inverted trapezoid, feature on the front of their snouts. The jaws of SCP-939 are lined with numerous red, faintly luminescent fang-like teeth, similar to those belonging to specimens of the genus Chauliodus, ranging from 11-57mm in length. Their jaws are encircled by heat-sensitive pit organs up to 5mm in diameter spaced at regular intervals. Regularly spaced eye spots 7mm in diameter, sensitive only to light and dark, run the length of their spined dorsal ridge. These spines may be anywhere from 12mm to 163mm long with an average diameter of 2 to 3mm and are believed to be sensitive to changes in air pressure and flow.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'll do a rewrite of that paragraph just as an example. Note that I have also corrected for plurality- when one sentence in a paragraph uses &quot;SCP-939 are&quot;, the next should not use &quot;SCP-939 is&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-939 are four limbed predators with opposable digits that are adapted for life within caves, having no eyes and translucent red skins that are highly permeable to moisture. SCP-939 average 215cm tall standing upright and weigh an average of 250kg though their weight is variable. Their heads contain no brain casing, but have faintly luminescent fangs and house organs used to sense changes in heat and air flow in their surroundings, which are used for navigation and tracking prey.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The need to know information there makes up less than half of the original paragraph, and the whole piece is like that. You've packed it with pointless biological analysis and scientific explanations for things that the reader IC does not need to know. The next paragraph could be cut in its entirety and change absolutely nothing. If you'd like, I can go through the rest, but I really don't feel like doing so.</p>

							</div>

								
